FBIS4-31499 "dreeu112_h_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-112 Daily Report 9 Jun 1994 HUNGARY Law on Foreigners `Violates' Rights Convention Law on Foreigners `Violates' Rights Convention LD0906113694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 0800 GMT 9 Jun 94 LD0906113694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Hungarian BFN [Text] According to officials of the Council of Europe, the new Hungarian law on foreigners violates two paragraphs of the European Human Rights Convention. The new law decrees that certain foreigners have to undergo an AIDS test; this is contrary to stipulations of the international agreement which bans discrimination and disallows judging applications for asylum on the basis of health. This is what the English-language BUDAPEST WEEK writes.
